title: Launch button won't work after patch
body: I have forced re-update and restarted my computer. I'm not sure what else to do has anyone else had this problem or know how to fix it.

replies.body: Bumping cause I have the same problem. Before the latest patch my workaround was to click 'launch' as soon as the launcher pops up. Somehow this worked before the patch but now everytime I hit launch it calculates file differences then nothing happens. Sometimes the EULA pops up but that's about it.
I can't launch my client too. Changed the DNS, re downloaded everything etc. HELP!

Have you tried running in admin mode?

Exactly what point does your client not work? Is it a RADS error?

So I have changed DNS like suggested. still nothing I have run in admin mode. forced re patch deleted. lol launcher. The EULA does appear after 5 minutes minutes when I accept the launcher still does nothing I wait longer press launch again and it just repeats the EULA and then does nothing this has been like this for 3 days now I suppose i will have to try redownloading and re installing
Did you try testing your connection with the network tool I linked you to?

Have you tried waiting around five minutes to see if the EULA eventually appears?

Have you tried running the patcher in admin mode?

Yeah the EULA does appear when I accept it does nothing have waited ages after that then nothing happens the EULA just keeps popping up after like 5 minutes after press launch but does nothing when I accept. I have tried running as administrator prior to the post.

That was a very confusing statement.

Anyway, go to [this page](https://support.riotgames.com/hc/en-us/articles/201752664-Troubleshooting-Connection-Issues) and try all the tips suggested there. Main one to look out for is the changing DNS.

If that fails, could you test your connection using [this tool](http://netalyzr.icsi.berkeley.edu/)? It's the one Riot gets you to use if they want to diagnose your connection. You need to have Java installed and enabled in order to use it.

Note any things which appear in red in the synopsis. **Do not post the entire log.** You may have already had to do this while using the troubleshooting page, so just use that if you still have it up. Also, could you provide me with your ISP and OS?

Best of luck.
